@@yThe Spirebound Conclave@@N

@@eThe Spirebound Conclave was a mountain academy in the Cinderteeth Range
chartered to preserve dangerous magical knowledge that lowland courts feared
and coveted. Its founding doctrine of Continuance held that no discovery,
oath, or lesson should die with its keeper.@@N

@@dThree internal factions divided the Conclave's approach:@@N

@@r  The Ember Canon @@d- will forged through suffering, tempered by fire.
@@l  The Prism Thesis @@d- memory stabilized through crystal harmonics.
@@e  The Pale Ledger  @@d- testimony preserved through spirit imprinting.@@N

@@yThe early sanctum was elegant and austere. Bells marked watches, apprentices
copied ledgers by candlelight, and tribunal mages debated ethics in vaulted
halls. But when border wars severed supply routes, the Conclave reframed
Continuance from scholarly ideal into survival engine.@@N

@@rIsolation demanded bodies. Volunteers were sought, then expected, then
quietly replaced by condemned debtors and political prisoners transferred
under sealed warrants. Some came from Midgaard's guild courts. Some from
the delta settlements that would become Kowloon. The warrants were
countersigned by magistrates whose successors now govern those cities.@@N

@@eThe Conclave used isolation and emergency governance to avoid accountability.
Its experiments produced Flamebound Sentinels from wounded veterans, Shadow
Stalkers from scout prototypes, and Spirit Mages from chained mnemonic
echoes. Each success demanded stronger ritual anchors and harsher sacrifice.@@N

@@dThe Prism Thesis faction also conducted field trials in remote forests,
implanting resonance crystals in root systems. When the Conclave collapsed,
those crystals were never retrieved. Over centuries they warped the
surrounding ecology into the corruption now known as the Withered Depths.
The Blightmother at its heart may be the final product of a Conclave
process that completed itself without human oversight.@@N

@@yThe catastrophe came when rival offices sabotaged each other's containment
during a seismic event. Regional powers buried the sanctum by policy. Its
institutional crimes created the Rivennid, fed the Withered Depths, and
left Midgaard and Kowloon sharing a guilt that both cities know and neither
will speak.@@N
